											<td width="100%" valign="top">					
												<!-- START NEWS AREAS-->
												<table width="90%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table width='100%' cellpadding='3' border='0'>
<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> FIERY AVENGER</td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'><body>

The Fiery Avenger, now a sub-quest for the Fiery Defender, is easily a paladin's
most difficult quest. Although the quest starts in air, it is best to begin
gathering the components of the quest beforehand.
<p>The first two components you must gather are the Soulfire and Ghoulbane,
which will serve to aquire the two blessing from Inte Akera, the quest giver. <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&amp;Id=834">Ghoulbane</a>
can be obtained through the Froglok Shin Lord in Upper Guk as his rare drop,
while Soulfire is obtained through the <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon/articledetails.asp?id=49">Zimels
Blade's</a> quest.
<p>The most tedious, and definatly hardest, part of the quest is obtaining the
completed Book of Scale. To obtain this you must first get each half of the
book. The first half, the 'torn, burnt book' can be found of Nagafen for those
below 53, and off Faydedar, Talendor, and Severilous for those above 53.<br>
The second half, the book of frost, is acquired off Lady Vox for those under 53,
and off Faydedar and Gorenaire for those above 53.
<p>To create the completed Book of Scale you must hand both book halves as well
as 1000pp to the bartender at the Blind Fish Tavern in Neriak. Remember to have
enough faction when doing this. You will know your faction is sufficient if she
will speak to you with a hail.
<p>After completing the Book of Scale, head to Ocean of Tears and hand it to the
Oracle. In return you will recieve Miragul's Phylactery. After recieving the
Phylactery go to the Everfrost ice caves, where you will find a Lich of Miragul
roaming about. Have an enchanter or necromancer charm the lich and hand him the
phylactery. This will spawn Miragul himself, who you must now slay. Miragul is
difficult and will require many prepared adventurers. He will drop the Robe of
Miragul and the Head of Miragul, the two items Inte Akera requires.
<p>Now that all items are prepared, go to the Plane of Air. You can spawn Inte
Akera by handing Dirkog Steelhand in the quest area 500pp. Inte Akera spawns on
the fourth island, so it is advised that you already be there to hand in the
items when completing the quest.
<p>First hand him the soulfire for your first blessing, then the ghoulbane for
your second. Hand both blessings back to Inte along with the head and robe of
Miragul to recieve the Fiery Avenger.</p>

</body></td>
</tr>
